# Example configuration file for go-ldap-proxy-cache
# This file documents the available command-line flags

# Proxy listen address (default: :3389)
# -proxy-addr :3389

# Backend LDAP server address (default: localhost:389)
# -ldap-server localhost:389

# Cache TTL duration (default: 15m)
# Examples: 15m, 1h, 30m, 2h30m
# -cache-ttl 15m

# Example usage:
# ./ldap-proxy -proxy-addr :3389 -ldap-server ldap.example.com:389 -cache-ttl 15m

# Note: The proxy acts as a transparent proxy, forwarding client credentials
# to the backend LDAP server. Clients should authenticate directly through the proxy.
